-- Hong Kong shares suffer worst week since May 2012
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Fri Mar 14, 2014 04:17AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Mar 14 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares fell to a six-week low on Friday, pulled down by index heavyweights Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK> and New World Development <0017.HK>.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> fell 1 percent to 21,539.49 points, its lowest close since Feb. 6. For the week, it fell 4.9 percent, its largest weekly loss since May 2012. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the top Chinese listings in Hong Kong fell 0.3 percent on the day and dropped 1.8 percent for the week, its biggest weekly loss since October 2013. Shares in China's largest listed Internet company Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK> fell 4.1 percent to a one-month low after the People's Bank of China demanded that payments made by certain online mobile methods be halted.[ID:nL3N0MB1D2]